Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.24,0:00:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, class...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.03,0:00:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me what the decision in the 1968 Stuttgart case was based upon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.00,0:00:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, what is this silence?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.17,0:00:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this a Zen temple in the Orient?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.05,0:00:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Eimer... I would like to\Nhear your answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.64,0:00:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.72,0:00:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... uh... That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.72,0:00:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone! Is there anyone\Nwho will break this silence?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.20,0:00:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the chronic latecomer is here at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.24,0:00:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You're 13 minutes late...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.41,0:00:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems your part-time pizza delivery job\Nwas awfully busy today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.04,0:01:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry... Professor... Kronecker...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.38,0:01:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.75,0:01:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,let me ask you a question\Nbefore you sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.21,0:01:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have enough strength\Nto tell me what the basis was
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.84,0:01:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for the decision in the Stuttgart case?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.97,0:01:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.64,0:01:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... yes. Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.06,0:01:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The accused claimed that\Nthe kidnapping was a sham
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.60,0:01:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the victim's death\Nhad been due to an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.06,0:01:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,After an investigation\Nof the crime scene
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.69,0:01:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it was found that the victim's death\Nhad indeed been accidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.24,0:01:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, based on the fact that the intent\Nto kill must be proven in a murder
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.37,0:01:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that a sentence\Nof 15 years was handed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.08,0:01:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good.\NSit down, Nina Fortner.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.34,0:01:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.63,0:03:23.18,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.72\fsp4.8\fad(1064,950)\bord0.48\be1\4a&H2a&\shad1.2\fs36\b0\fnSouvenir Lt BT\pos(397.866,475.2)\c&H000000&\1a&H00&}Heidelberg,\N(Germany)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.63,0:03:23.18,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fsp4.8\fad(772,691)\bord0\be1\4a&H2a&\fs36\b0\fnSouvenir Lt BT\c&HF5F7F3&\pos(397.866,475.2)\shad1.2\4a&HFF&}Heidelberg,\N(Germany)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.35,0:03:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved us, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.80,0:03:28.77,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur3.6\fad(950,0)\bord0\fs55.2\shad3\fnBitstream Vera Sans\b1\c&HFCFCFA&\pos(391.466,432)\alpha&H80&\1a&HFF&}The Girl of Heidelberg
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.80,0:03:28.77,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.72\fad(950,0)\bord0\fs55.2\shad3\fnBitstream Vera Sans\b1\c&HFCFCFA&\pos(391.466,432)}The Girl of Heidelberg
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.94,0:03:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If no one had been able to\Ngive him the answer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.10,0:03:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Kronecker would have probably\Ndemanded 50-page reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.61,0:03:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,50 pages, if we were lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.74,0:03:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to treat Nina, to whom we're\Ngreatly indebted, to something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.74,0:03:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You can come, can't you Nina?\NJust the two of us...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:44.20,signs,,0,0,15,,{\blur0.72\fad(280,250)\fs43.2\fscx115.314\bord0\shad0.6\c&HFEFFFE&\fnAvantGarde Md BT\pos(390.4,471.601)\4c&H5C5D5B&}Nina Fortner
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.20,0:03:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}I'm sorry, Peter.\NI have a club meeting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.87,0:03:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.37,0:03:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,She turned you down again...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.63,0:03:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter, how many times was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.38,0:03:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.76,0:03:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to see if there's anyone\Nwho can get Nina to agree to a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.14,0:04:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.57,0:04:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! If I'm late with my deliveries, I'm going to get it from the manager again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.42,0:04:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.09,0:04:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, am I hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.76,0:04:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my, the neighbors\Ncan probably hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a young lady now.\NIt's not becoming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.88,0:04:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Go and wash your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.93,0:04:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.18,0:04:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Mom, did you\Ncolor your hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.56,0:04:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks good, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.81,0:04:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly! You shouldn't be dying\Nyour hair so bright, at your age!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.06,0:04:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong, Dad.\NShe looks lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.23,0:04:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not going to\Na masquerade party, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.65,0:05:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be wonderful\Nfor Mom to be young forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.74,0:05:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.95,0:05:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes... Speaking of masquerades...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.25,0:05:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw some kids in costumes today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.08,0:05:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes...\NIt's the St. Hadrian Costume Parade.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.75,0:05:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I had dressed up\Nlike that when I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.42,0:05:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They were so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.51,0:05:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh... you did dress up\Nin a costume.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.97,0:05:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.89,0:05:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Oh... that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.48,0:05:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... It's around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.11,0:05:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here it is!\NHere, look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.03,0:05:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.32,0:05:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You were so excited\Nand made such a fuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.66,0:05:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.45,0:05:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.59,0:06:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A costume parade?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.31,0:06:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Distant spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.64,0:06:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I forlornly wait for a spring\Nthat will never come... Hannah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.11,0:06:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Hannah... Will you hurry\Nand get over your broken heart?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.49,0:06:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me send you\Nthe world's most beautiful flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.16,0:06:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born to blanket you in flowers...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.08,0:06:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow... I wonder who sent this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.17,0:06:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Aha!\NI'm very impressed, Peter!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.72,0:06:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How have you been, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.39,0:06:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, well, I've been very well,\Nthankfully, Dr. Gaitel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.18,0:06:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.81,0:06:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I could tell by the look\Non your face when you entered
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.19,0:06:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this counseling room\Nthat your were doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.86,0:07:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And do you no longer\Nhave that dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.69,0:07:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Of that monster appearing\Nout of the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.57,0:07:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I've been sleeping so well,\NI have no time to dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.03,0:07:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder why I was plagued by\Nsuch a dream night after night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.83,0:07:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's common for people to become\Ninsecure during their student years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.63,0:07:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams of the future become\Nconfused with other insecurities,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.42,0:07:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and you lose sight of who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.63,0:07:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But what you are is something\Nyou can spend your whole life
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.26,0:07:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to learn, and never discover.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.05,0:07:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All you can do now is be prepared\Nto spend your whole life searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.18,0:07:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and do only what you can do\Ntoward your future.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.06,0:07:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I will do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.23,0:07:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to become a public prosecutor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.36,0:07:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.90,0:07:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I think we can end\Nour counseling session for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.36,0:07:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.83,0:07:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina Fortner... Such a cheerful girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.75,0:08:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't help but feel\Nthat her cheerfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.04,0:08:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is a reaction to something\Nshe's running away from.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.01,0:08:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Some... vast... darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.76,0:08:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.89,0:08:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say that.\NDon't act so innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.56,0:08:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world\Nare you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.64,0:08:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"I was born to\Nblanket you in flowers..."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.44,0:08:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought you had\Nthe makings of a poet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.90,0:08:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.74,0:08:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be able to come up with words\Nlike those even if I stood on my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.87,0:08:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.07,0:08:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.62,0:08:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I've given my email address\Nto only my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.95,0:08:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.33,0:08:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn. All I know is that\NI have another rival in love!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.01,0:08:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Who in the world could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.09,0:08:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This bizarre murder\Nthat took place in Munich...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.60,0:08:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator,\Nafter shooting the parents to death,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.14,0:09:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,strangled the two children with a rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.19,0:09:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'd like you to explain the ruling\Nof the judge from the court records...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.95,0:09:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina Fortner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.03,0:09:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you not understand the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.41,0:09:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No... uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.12,0:09:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The trial was focused on\Nthe cold-blooded murder
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.96,0:09:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of a whole family...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.30,0:09:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.72,0:09:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.22,0:09:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? There are times\Nyou can't answer either, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.44,0:09:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.27,0:09:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.61,0:09:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.03,0:09:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.41,0:09:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to go to the infirmary?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.83,0:09:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.04,0:10:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I just felt a little ill...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.46,0:10:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,After listening to the professor's story...\Nsuddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.21,0:10:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You mean that bizarre\Nmassacre of that family?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.67,0:10:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.38,0:10:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you were awfully brave,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.85,0:10:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're more sensitive\Nthan I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.52,0:10:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see a horror movie\Nthat terrified you as a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.77,0:10:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! I'll bet that counselor,\NDr. Gaitel, would probably say...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.94,0:10:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"If you look back on why this happened, you'll find it was nothing significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.86,0:10:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why don't you think back\Non your childhood..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.28,0:10:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.78,0:10:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,don't remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.54,0:10:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember anything\Nbefore the age of ten...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.52,0:11:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,My memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.77,0:11:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My childhood memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.57,0:11:21.07,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.72\fsp4.8\fad(1064,950)\bord0.48\be1\4a&H2a&\shad1.2\fs36\b0\fnSouvenir Lt BT\pos(385.866,475.2)\c&H000000&\1a&H00&}Köln,\N(Germany)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.57,0:11:21.07,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fsp4.8\fad(772,691)\bord0\be1\4a&H2a&\fs36\b0\fnSouvenir Lt BT\c&HF5F7F3&\pos(385.866,475.2)\shad1.2\4a&HFF&}Köln,\N(Germany)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.37,0:11:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.37,0:11:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They were a very nice couple...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.66,0:11:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,To think they were killed like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.08,0:11:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Children?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.84,0:11:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, now that you mention it,\Nthey had a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.71,0:11:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,His name was Michael, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.76,0:11:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They lived together about two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.09,0:11:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.14,0:11:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Was there a boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.18,0:11:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there was.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.72,0:11:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't his name Michael?\NHe was around fourteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.35,0:11:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Michael, you say?\NI seem to remember him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.27,0:11:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Are you the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.32,0:12:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Michael Reichmann.\NHe was a student in my class.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.91,0:12:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But he didn't leave\Nmuch of an impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.75,0:12:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm embarrassed to say this,\Nbut I don't remember him well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.79,0:12:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if he had any friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.54,0:12:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And, there are no records...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.59,0:12:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything burned\Nin a fire six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.51,0:12:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There definitely was a boy named Michael living here in Cologne until six years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.39,0:12:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And... Michael's real name...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.31,0:12:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.23,0:12:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've used that name before...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.20,0:12:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who... are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.99,0:12:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But what's the use in knowing that?\NWhat's the use?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He is a serial-killer who is a twin...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.83,0:12:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's all there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.04,0:12:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.13,0:13:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A twin!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.47,0:13:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What about his sister?\NWhere did his twin sister go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.85,0:13:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,"I will come for you soon..."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.73,0:13:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.10,0:13:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll come for me soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.44,0:13:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.94,0:13:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A child?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.65,0:13:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there was...\Nabout 7 or 8 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.78,0:13:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So Mr. and Mrs. Heinemann,\Nwho were killed, were fostering a boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.79,0:13:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What was he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.41,0:13:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What was he like?\NThat was a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.42,0:13:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And he only lived with them\Nabout a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.34,0:13:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember\Nanything about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.01,0:13:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't that boy have a sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.84,0:13:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.39,0:13:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I just want to forget about\Nwhat happened to that couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.14,0:13:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I even thought about moving away\Nafter it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.94,0:14:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I know about that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.20,0:14:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.70,0:14:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just about to\Nfix some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.12,0:14:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.38,0:14:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... yes. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.59,0:14:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.99,0:14:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Please have some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.87,0:14:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.25,0:15:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a doctor, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.05,0:15:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.63,0:15:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Dr. Tenma, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.39,0:15:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He's coming for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.18,0:15:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.35,0:15:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.52,0:15:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an anonymous message.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.94,0:15:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You look so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.81,0:15:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not thinking a prince\Non a white horse
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.48,0:15:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,will be coming for you, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.28,0:15:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you jealous?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.36,0:15:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go,\Ndaydreaming again, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.66,0:15:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"I was born to blanket you in flowers..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.20,0:15:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There aren't any kids\Nwho talk like that today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.38,0:15:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, listen. Haven't you noticed\Na strange boy in class recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.01,0:15:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Yes, I have!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.38,0:15:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who calmly sits in\Nthat "legendary seat"in Room 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.84,0:15:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're bound to be called on\Nby the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.64,0:15:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, he's never called on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.14,0:15:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. And do you know,\Nhe stares at Nina all through class!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.85,0:15:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.27,0:16:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.44,0:16:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You know!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.98,0:16:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Your prince on the white horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.66,0:16:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy was extremely grateful\Nto you, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.12,0:16:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He said you were the one who saved him;\Nyou meant more to him than a parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.83,0:16:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What name did he go by?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.08,0:16:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.54,0:16:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But he said\Nit wasn't his real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.38,0:16:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He trusted you enough\Nto tell you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.56,0:16:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That Franz, who had shown up\Nout of the blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.73,0:16:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,was cared for by\NMr. and Mrs. Heinemann,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.44,0:16:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,who lived in the flat across the hall,\Nfor a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.07,0:16:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No, actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.61,0:16:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it was 13 months\Nfrom March 1987 to April 1988.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.12,0:16:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, one day, he suddenly vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.70,0:17:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He was very bright.\NAnd he was well-mannered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.13,0:17:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he used to\Ncome to this apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.71,0:17:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.26,0:17:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I lived alone so I always welcomed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.09,0:17:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He sat in that seat\Nand spent his time studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.01,0:17:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In no time, he had mastered the English and French that I taught him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.52,0:17:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time he disappeared,\Nhe was fluent in both.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.61,0:17:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That 12-year-old boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.57,0:17:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything else\Nyou remember about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.62,0:17:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He always listened closely\Nto my stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.41,0:17:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What stories do you think\Nhe was most interested in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.58,0:17:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.84,0:17:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,War stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.84,0:17:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,War?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.55,0:17:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,During World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.22,0:17:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on the crew of a U-boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.97,0:17:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,His favorite story\Nwas about the time
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.43,0:18:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we were attacked by a destroyer\Nof the Allied Forces...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.10,0:18:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We were at a depth of 120 meters...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.31,0:18:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We were attacked by the enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.77,0:18:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and although we had suffered\Na fatal blow, we kept going.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.82,0:18:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside that groaning ship,\Nwe all waited in terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.37,0:18:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We returned from that living hell\N38 hours later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.87,0:18:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,An ordinary child would probably
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.00,0:18:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,look at this as\Nanother adventure story...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.59,0:18:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But that boy was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.59,0:18:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What he was\Nmost interested in was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.26,0:18:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.76,0:18:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Extreme terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.01,0:18:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the reaction of a person\Nstanding on the edge of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.10,0:18:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That was his only interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.52,0:18:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He took pleasure in terror!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.69,0:18:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What sort of expression did he\Nhave while listening to your stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.74,0:19:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably had a gleam in his eye,\Nand a smile on his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.33,0:19:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.75,0:19:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I am blind, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.29,0:19:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I know neither his real name,\Nnor what he looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.09,0:19:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, you said that boy\Ntrusted me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.72,0:19:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He never trusts anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.10,0:19:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one person\Nhe's ever trusted...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.85,0:19:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,his sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.86,0:19:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm looking for that sister!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.61,0:19:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he would go and collect her\Nwhen she turned twenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.95,0:19:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.12,0:19:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To Heidelberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.87,0:19:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.04,0:19:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ride carefully on your scooter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.29,0:19:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.54,0:19:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.13,0:19:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.76,0:19:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Good bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.85,0:20:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it's time...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.27,0:20:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.36,0:20:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We decided, didn't we?\NThat we'd tell her on her 20th birthday
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.53,0:20:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that she's not our child.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.04,0:20:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait, I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.87,0:20:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?\NYou wanted to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.46,0:20:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We told him you'd wait for him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.63,0:20:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't screw up,\Nwith your "prince on a white horse."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.59,0:20:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.09,0:20:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Clara! Beata!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.56,0:20:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,How could they do this\Nbehind my back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.23,0:20:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.94,0:20:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.50,0:21:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How do you do...\NYou're Nina Fortner?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.17,0:21:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.17,0:21:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... I'm Otto Hubermann...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.67,0:21:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.74,0:21:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who is he...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.49,0:21:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.45,0:21:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've seen him... somewhere... before...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.55,0:22:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.82,0:22:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- Nina!\N- Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.44,0:22:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina! What's wrong?\NAre you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.44,0:22:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- Nina, wake up!\N- Nina! Nina!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.11,0:22:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina, wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.11,0:22:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina. Hey, Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.29,0:22:36.96,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And slowly, you come to realize
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.50,0:22:44.38,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's all as it should be
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.26,0:22:53.81,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You can only do so much
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.98,0:22:59.40,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}If you're game enough
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.82,0:23:07.20,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You could place your trust in me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.20,0:23:16.29,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}For the love of life
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.42,0:23:21.63,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}There's a trade off
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.42,0:23:28.39,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}We could lose it all
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.39,0:23:33.31,ED-ENG,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But we'll go down fighting
